Race.SpecificTitle: PW School District No. 3 -- 12.09 Mills Continuation - SB - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Parishwide School District No. 3 Proposition 
(Millage Continuation)
Race.FullText: Shall Parishwide School District No. 3 of the Parish of Tensas, State of Louisiana (the "District"), levy a special tax of twelve and nine hundredths (12.09) mills on all property subject to taxation in the District (an estimated $675,225 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2020 and ending with the year 2029, for the purpose of giving additional support to the public schools in the District, including providing funds for acquiring, constructing, improving, maintaining and/or operating public school buildings, facilities and equipment, said millage to represent a seventy-nine hundredths of a mill (.79) increase (due to reappraisal) over the 11.3 mills tax authorized to be levied through the year 2019 pursuant to an election held on April 4, 2009?
